'''Lake Lanutavake''' ({{lang-fr|Lac Lanutavake}}) is a small crater lake surrounded by jungle on the southwest side of [[Wallis (island)|Wallis]] (Uvea) in the Pacific. It lies to the northeast of [[Fineveke]].<ref name="GM">{{cite map|title= Maps|publisher=[[Google Maps]]}}</ref> Like [[Lake Lalolalo]], there is a rumor that the US military dumped equipment in the lake at the end of World War II.<ref name="Stanley1996">{{cite book|last=Stanley|first=David|title=South Pacific Handbook|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T9uXirhyw7YC&pg=PA483|accessdate=29 April 2012|year=1996|publisher=David Stanley|isbn=978-1-56691-040-8|page=483}}</ref>

