'''Povardarie''' ({{lang-mk|Повардарие}}) is a geographic region in the central part of the [[Republic of Macedonia]], and includes all of the canyons, mountains and valleys through which the river [[Vardar]] flows. 

Term is used in names of [[Diocese of Povardarie]] of the [[Macedonian Orthodox Church]] and "Eparchy of Veles and Povardarie" of the [[Orthodox Ohrid Archbishopric]].

