The '''Tirona Highway''' is a two-to-four lane,  primary highway in [[Cavite]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2016%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/cavite.htm|title=Cavite|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>. The road was named for Filipino revolutionary leader  [[Daniel Tirona]].

The road is a component of the '''National Route 62 (N62)''' of the [[Philippine highway network]].

